OL,3,CYour Granada Weather Team
OL,5,FFrequently recognised for her sunny
OL,6,F"Bye Bye" sign-off, Emma is one of the
OL,7,Flongest serving weather presenters at
OL,8,FITV.JShe started as a colourful,
OL,9,Fquirky regular on national breakfast
OL,10,Ftelevision, and has had her head in
OL,11,Fthe clouds - and ITV Weather regions -
OL,12,Fsince 1992, also presenting
OL,13,Fcountryside programmes. Emma's always
OL,14,Fhad a keen interest in the weather,
OL,15,Fespecially since she hails from the
OL,16,FNorth West where there is rather a lot
OL,17,Fof it...JShe originally trained to be
OL,18,Fa vet, but side-stepped into TV. As
OL,19,Fshe made the leap from vet to met, she
OL,20,Ffound that working with exotic species
OL,21,Fgave her quite a good grounding for a
OL,22,Fcareer in television... Emma has done
OL,23,Fevery job behind the camera, and
OL,24,Fworked as a radio journalist before
OL,25,Fachieving her ambition of joining the
OL,26,FITV Weather team - and for many years,
